## Dead Ends
- Retagging the existing public image was abandoned because the image itself was missing runtime pieces and selected a broken startup path on GB300.
- Adding only `pytest` was abandoned because it exposed the stale `quack-kernels` / `nvidia-cutlass-dsl` mismatch.
- Adding only `pytest` plus `quack-kernels==0.4.1` was abandoned because the image then reached the Kimi K2.5 ViT profiling path and tripped FA4's CUTE arch assertion on SM103.
- Adding a runtime manifest argument such as `--mm-encoder-attn-backend=TRITON_ATTN` was considered but not used for this commit because the user asked for an exact copy of `v050-dflash-vllm` with only the image changed. Putting the default-backend workaround into the image keeps the Kubernetes manifest clone exact while still avoiding the failing default on SM103.

